###Next Test, Smoothie...

Tap water isn't the best test of a filter's capability so it was time to move onto something harder.
Smoothie anyone?
Since I wasn't familiar with the brand I wasn't confidient on how it would fair under this test.

<%= partial "partials/image.erb", locals: {
    src: "IMG_20170410_194936-2.jpg",
    alt: "Bovon Water Straw Test 2 Smoothie"} %>

I was prepared to ruin this straw in the name of science.
This water straw had other plans though and saw straight through my doubt.

<%= partial "partials/image.erb", locals: {
    src: "IMG_20170410_195705-2.jpg",
    alt: "Bovon Water Straw Test 2 Smoothie Final"} %>

Amazingly, I tasted clean water through the straw and there was no taste at all.
I'll be honest that I was impressed.

Next I had to work to clean the filter which took a bit of extra work due to tough test it went through.
I ran water through the top of the filter and blew into the top several times.
Then I let it sit in a glass of water.
The particles slowly flowed out of the straw to the bottom of the cup after sitting 15 minutes or so.
Then I took the filter out of the water and let it sit overnight to dry out.
Once the straw dried out I put the top and bottom cap on and stored the straw.

